{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":12630,"record_hash":"sha256:f2e1cf29f28555549f35243b5ee9c4ba8feb7dc10427ed58274055bb8d7a957c","timestamp":"2026-05-07T22:03:03.191Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"{\"status\":{\"[REDACTED:entropy]\":{\"completed\":\"::code-comment{title=\\\"[P2] Settings are touched before agentlog validation\\\" body=\\\"`handle_args` loads `AppSettings` before the feature-gated `AgentLog` branch, but agentlog returns before metrics setup and does not use those settings. That load creates the settings file when absent and can migrate legacy settings, so `but -C <repo> agentlog capture ...` can fail on unrelated config or create config files before validating `--agent`, `--transcript-path`, or the repo/transcript inputs.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/lib.rs\\\" start=119 priority=2 confidence=0.91}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P3] Target validation happens after transcript work\\\" body=\\\"`target` is carried as a raw string through `capture`, and `Target::parse` is only called inside `write_capture` after the transcript path is canonicalized, the full file is read and parsed, and transcript cwd values are validated. This makes invalid `--target` errors depend on unrelated filesystem/transcript state and diverges from the capture workflow's resolve-target-before-read order. Parsing the target before transcript I/O would simplify the trace and make validation order predictable.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs\\\" start=37 priority=3 confidence=0.86}\\n\\n::code-comment{title=\\\"[P3] Source path is stored lossily\\\" body=\\\"The canonical transcript path is converted with `to_string_lossy()` before being written to GitMeta. On Unix, a non-UTF-8 transcript path will be stored with replacement characters while the `session_key` fallback uses the raw encoded path bytes, leaving GitMeta with a source path that cannot reliably be compared to or reopened as the original path. Prefer rejecting non-UTF-8 paths explicitly or storing a reversible encoded form.\\\" file=\\\"/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/capture.rs\\\" start=47 priority=3 confidence=0.8}\"}},\"timed_out\":false}","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-07T22:03:03.191Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}